abstract: In a volatile primary with no true front-runner, Democrats face the prospect of a monthslong delegate battle that would also feature a lengthy public airing of the party’s ideological fissures.
snippet: In a volatile primary with no true front-runner, Democrats face the prospect of a monthslong delegate battle that would also feature a lengthy public airing of the party’s ideological fissures.
lead_paragraph: MASON CITY, Iowa — With just under two months until the Iowa caucuses, the already-volatile Democratic presidential race has grown even more unsettled, setting the stage for a marathon nominating contest between the party’s moderate and liberal factions.

abstract: A fact-based story starring Samuel L. Jackson and Anthony Mackie was supposed to hit theaters Friday. Then a complaint by a relative of the film’s hero gave Apple second thoughts.
snippet: A fact-based story starring Samuel L. Jackson and Anthony Mackie was supposed to hit theaters Friday. Then a complaint by a relative of the film’s hero gave Apple second thoughts.
lead_paragraph: Apple has struggled to find its footing as it tries to go Hollywood. Critics were lukewarm at best about “The Morning Show,” the star-studded, big-budget flagship series on Apple TV Plus, the streaming platform that went live Nov. 1. And now one of Apple’s first films, “The Banker,” starring Samuel L. Jackson and Anthony Mackie, is in limbo after the company pulled it from a theatrical run that was scheduled to start Friday.

abstract: In his first TV interview as a presidential candidate, Mr. Bloomberg said other Democrats “had a chance to go out and make a lot of money” themselves, and then use it to fund their campaigns.
snippet: In his first TV interview as a presidential candidate, Mr. Bloomberg said other Democrats “had a chance to go out and make a lot of money” themselves, and then use it to fund their campaigns.
lead_paragraph: Michael R. Bloomberg on Friday brushed back critiques about his wealth and bristled at the suggestion that he was using it to buy success in the 2020 presidential race, arguing that other Democrats who have complained about his entry into their party’s primary could have taken it upon themselves to earn their own personal fortunes, as he had done.

abstract: A writer followed a Navajo high school basketball team for a season. Here is a tale from one road trip.
snippet: A writer followed a Navajo high school basketball team for a season. Here is a tale from one road trip.
lead_paragraph: The sky was milk white and vaulted. A squall tugged at sagebrush and sent dust devils spinning off the mesas. Millenniums of rain and the holy winds, the Niłch’i Diyini, had carved the washes and gulches and canyons that folded into the skin of this land.

abstract: The former New York City mayor unveiled a detailed plan for addressing gun violence in Aurora, Colo., the site of a 2012 massacre at a movie theater.
snippet: The former New York City mayor unveiled a detailed plan for addressing gun violence in Aurora, Colo., the site of a 2012 massacre at a movie theater.
lead_paragraph: Michael R. Bloomberg proposed a sweeping array of federal gun-control measures on Thursday, calling for a national gun licensing system and stricter background checks, hundreds of millions of dollars in new enforcement spending and the passage of a federal red-flag law that would allow courts to temporarily confiscate firearms from people deemed dangerous.

abstract: We invited teenagers to show us aspects of their lives that adults often overlook or misunderstand. Here’s what they think we should know.
snippet: We invited teenagers to show us aspects of their lives that adults often overlook or misunderstand. Here’s what they think we should know.
lead_paragraph: Over 2,200 students took us up on our second annual challenge to “show us your generation” — to photograph aspects of teenage life that push back against media and adult stereotypes and make the portrait of Generation Z more interesting, nuanced, complete or real.

abstract: As the party reckons with the likelihood of an all-white candidate lineup for the December debate, Cory Booker and Julián Castro see fund-raising gains.
snippet: As the party reckons with the likelihood of an all-white candidate lineup for the December debate, Cory Booker and Julián Castro see fund-raising gains.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Senator Cory Booker strode onstage here with a question, one that voters, activists and disgruntled members of the Democratic National Committee are also asking in the wake of Senator Kamala Harris’s sudden departure from the 2020 race.

abstract: Our critics chose the best albums of the year — a format that is in an increasingly fragile state in pop music.
snippet: Our critics chose the best albums of the year — a format that is in an increasingly fragile state in pop music.
lead_paragraph: The best pop of 2019 didn’t try to reach everyone. It was the work of bedroom-studio conspirators, of songwriters confronting their traumas and aspirations, of old hands challenging themselves and newcomers determined to warp accepted boundaries: artists working to please themselves at a time when gatekeepers can easily be bypassed. If it turned out that those private outpourings resonated with a wide audience, all the better — but that wasn’t the only goal.
